                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/7–2849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Paul A. Porter</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lausanne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-28T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 28, 1949—11 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Palun1">Palun</gloss> 252. As result urging by general
                    committee, chiefs all Arab delegations have agreed cable their governments
                    recommending that favorable reply be given to Israeli <hi rend="italic"
                        >démarche</hi> through <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss>s re reuniting
                    separated families and that steps be taken to begin reunion.</p>
                <p>Also as result urging by general committee Israeli delegation has agreed request
                    Israeli Government give favorable consideration Arab desires re conditions for
                    reunion families based on oriental concept of family unit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Porter</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
